The paper proposes a framework for validating qualitative properties of machine learning models, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. The paper does not focus on a specific application area, but rather presents a general framework that can be applied to various use-cases and datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
